args:
One of those intruders was a combat
android that will surely prove a powerful
asset to our glorious Dyrenell Empire.
Capture it alive, no matter the cost!
*huff* *pant* Sorry for the wait!\nYou miss us?
Not especially—and I certainly didn't miss\nthe imperials who are clearly chasing you.
Yeah, sorry 'bout that. They're probably\ngoing to be on us at any moment.
Laxi's got the idea: It's fight or die!\nYou hold this side of things while I\ntry to wrap around the flank, yeah?

Understood. Prioritizing swift elimination
before reinforcements can be summoned.
Mascula, requesting Eden mode activation.
▷Right. I'm on it.◁
By the heavens... What IS that thing?!\nI've never heard of a combat android\nwith such powers!
▷Crossing system zenith in 60... LAXI!\nWhatever you're gonna do, do it fast!◁\nI am aware of the time constraints.
We'll hold the line, Lieutenant!\nGo summon reinforcements!
Are you insane?! You'll all be dead\nby the time they arrive!
My life belongs to the Dyrenell Empire,\nand she cannot afford to lose you here.\nGo, for the sake of the Empire's future!
We shall sing songs of your sacrifice,\nsoldier... I'll return as soon as I can!
If we fall today, our bodies will be the\nbones for Dyrenell's glorious tomorrow!
▷They'll die to protect their leader...◁\nIrrelevant. All hostiles will be purged.
▷No! Laxi, wait!◁\nOverruled. There is no time.
L-Lieutenant... The rest is...\nin your hands...
Eden mode...destabilizing?\nMascula, what have you done?\n▷Huh? I haven't done anything!◁
Mana kiln strain increasing.\n▷Uh oh. At this rate...◁
▷(But why? So long as I have the will to\nfight, Eden mode should work fine!)◁
▷(I swore that I would fight,\nbut just now, I hesitated.)◁
The android's wide open! Capture it!
▷(These people have their ideals,\nand the resolve to defend their allies\nwith their lives. I can't keep...)◁
▷Laxi, I'm sorry. I just can't...◁\nAffirmative. I now understand the\ndestabilizing factor inhibiting Eden mode.
Your synchronization with my will is\nincomplete. You have the resolve to fight,\nbut not the true desire.
Dammit, they're focusing their attacks on\nMascula and Laxi! Hold on, guys! I'm co—
All right! We bagged the sylvan!
Advantage lost. Initiating tactical retreat.\n▷No, we can't leave! They've got Luca!◁
You think you're the first android that\nwe've dealt with? ...Keep it up, men!\nShut that hunk of junk down!
I didn't shield YOU... I just...\nI wanted the other guy to make it.
Without him, we're stuck with a world\nfull of people acting on hatred alone...\nPeople like I used to be...
A world like that...will never know peace...
You would entrust the hope of a peaceful\nfuture to a combat android like Mascula?
Heh. L-looks like it... Now go...\nGet out of here while you can...
If they catch you, they'll do far worse than\nwhat's in store for the sylvan and me...
▷We won't allow you to be\ntaken prisoner for our sake!◁
That meddling fool... You won't be\nso fortunate this time!
Tactical retreat engaged.\n▷Laxi, no! We can't!◁\nWe have no choice.
Damn, we lost the android. ...After it, men!\nAnd bring that scum with you!
No hostiles in range. All clear.
▷I'm sorry, Laxi. I really screwed up.◁\nConditional affirmative.
▷That man was taken prisoner because of\nus—because of me. And so was Luca.◁
Regret is a luxury we lack the time for.\nHowever, if you intend to stop fighting,\nI will continue to fight alone.
▷...No. No matter how much it hurts,\nI won't let you do this on your own.◁
▷I want to help save them.◁\nUnderstood. Then I will trust you.
▷Then let's keep pushing forward until I\nfind the way to synchronize with you!◁
